Indosat, Medco Energi, Wijaya Karya: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-08-16T01:18:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-16/indosat-medco-energi-wijaya-karya-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  rose 1.8 percent to 3,960.02.  Energy companies: Crude oil futures advanced 2.9 percent to
$87.88 a barrel in New York yesterday and traded at $87.36 at
9:10 a.m. in  Singapore . PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC IJ),
 Indonesia ’s biggest listed oil company, climbed 1 percent to
2,600 rupiah and PT Energi Mega Persada (ENRG IJ), the second-
largest, rose 2.4 percent to 210 rupiah.  PT Adaro Energy (ADRO IJ): First-half net income at the
nation’s second-largest coal producer more than doubled from the
same period a year earlier to $268 million, the company said.
Adaro rose 1.1 percent to 2,350 rupiah.  PT Indosat (ISAT IJ): Indonesia’s second-biggest telephone
company said first-half net income rose 138 percent from a year
earlier to 681.9 billion rupiah ($80 million). Revenue increased
4 percent to 10.05 trillion rupiah, the company said in a
statement. Indosat jumped 5.5 percent to 5,750 rupiah.  PT Kawasan Industri Jababeka (KIJA IJ): The industrial
estate developer is seeking to raise 1.5 trillion rupiah selling
6.04 billion new shares in a rights offer in September, it said
in a statement published in  Bisnis Indonesia . Jababeka, as the
company is known, will use the proceeds to fund plans to acquire
PT Banten West Java Tourism Development and PT Tanjung Lesung
Leisure Industry, the statement said. Jababeka advanced 6.7
percent to 191 rupiah.  PT Wijaya Karya (WIKA IJ): The state-owned construction
company received a 500 billion rupiah loan from IKB Deutsche
Industriebank AG which will be used to finance the construction
of a power plant in Bali, Investor Daily Indonesia reported,
citing Wijaya Corporate Secretary Natal Argawan. Wijaya Karya
was unchanged at 610 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
